### 3.2. Garbage collection#garbage-collection

 An [XMLHttpRequest](#xmlhttprequest) object must not be garbage collected if its
[state](#concept-xmlhttprequest-state) is either
opened with the [send() flag](#send-flag) set,
headers received, or loading, and it has one or more
[event listeners](https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#concept-event-listener)
registered whose type is one of
[readystatechange](#event-xhr-readystatechange),
[progress](#event-xhr-progress),
[abort](#event-xhr-abort),
[error](#event-xhr-error),
[load](#event-xhr-load),
[timeout](#event-xhr-timeout), and
[loadend](#event-xhr-loadend).

 If an [XMLHttpRequest](#xmlhttprequest) object is garbage collected while its connection is still open, the user
agent must [terminate](https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#fetch-controller-terminate) the [XMLHttpRequest](#xmlhttprequest) object’s
[fetch controller](#xmlhttprequest-fetch-controller).

